# Pull request template

When opening or drafting a pull request, **always use and follow** [.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md](.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md).

- **Summary**: Provide a brief description of what the PR does.
- **Type of change**: Tick one of Bug fix, New feature, Documentation, Refactor / chore.
- **Checklist**: Ensure all items are addressed (conventions, `bun run typecheck`, Notion/config checks if relevant, linked issue).
- **Additional notes**: Add any optional context.

Do not open or submit a PR without filling out the template; complete every section that applies.
